#: ../../source/help/settings/channel-settings.md
msgid "Channel Notification Preferences"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/settings/channel-settings.md:6
msgid ""
"Notification preferences can be modified for each channel of which you "
"are a member."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/settings/channel-settings.md
msgid "Send Desktop Notifications"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/settings/channel-settings.md:9
msgid ""
"By default, the desktop notification preference assigned in Account "
"Settings is used for all channels. To customize the desktop notification "
"preference for each channel, click the channel name at the top of the "
"center pane to access the drop-down menu, then click Notification "
"Preferences > Send Desktop Notifications."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/settings/channel-settings.md
msgid "Mark Channel Unread"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/settings/channel-settings.md:12
msgid ""
"Customize what activity causes the channel name to be bolded by accessing"
" the channel name drop-down menu, then click Notification Preferences > "
"Mark Channel Unread."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/settings/channel-settings.md
msgid "Channel Header"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/settings/channel-settings.md:15
msgid ""
"The header is the text that appears next to the channel name at the top "
"of the screen. It can be used to summarize the channel topic or provide "
"links to frequently accessed documents. Any channel member can set the "
"channel header by clicking the channel name at the top of the center pane"
" to access the drop-down menu, then click  Set Channel Header."
msgstr ""

